comments.body:
Thanks for reaching and apologies for the longer silence; we've been really busy.  The `--context` option along with the `context` commands relate to Docker Swarm which is something Podman does not support.

In your specific case `--context=default` is something that Podman could support (i.e., default context).  I also think that Podman could do a better job at error reporting and report that `docker context` isn't supported because of Swarm.

@containers/podman-maintainers PTAL
